    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the difference between a VRC and a freight elevator?",
      "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "VRCs move materials only and cannot carry people. They are governed by ASME B20.1 (conveyor standard). Freight elevators move materials and people, and are governed by ASME A17.1 (elevator standard). VRCs have simpler code requirements, shorter permitting timelines, lower installation cost, and do not require a machine room or hoistway. Freight elevators require full elevator code compliance, an elevator contractor license, annual inspections, and typically a pit and overhead machine room." }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is the weight capacity of a VRC?",
